name: r-emayili
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.7.10" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-emayili
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/emayili_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/emayili/emayili_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 847c45e0d4514b7aa44f0869905812070314bce8318f669946ca205d0f944b46

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-base64enc
    - r-commonmark
    - r-curl >=4.0
    - r-digest
    - r-dplyr
    - r-glue
    - r-htmltools
    - r-httr
    - r-logger
    - r-magrittr
    - r-mime
    - r-purrr
    - r-rmarkdown
    - r-rvest
    - r-stringi
    - r-stringr
    - r-tidyr
    - r-urltools
    - r-xfun
    - r-xml2
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-base64enc
    - r-commonmark
    - r-curl >=4.0
    - r-digest
    - r-dplyr
    - r-glue
    - r-htmltools
    - r-httr
    - r-logger
    - r-magrittr
    - r-mime
    - r-purrr
    - r-rmarkdown
    - r-rvest
    - r-stringi
    - r-stringr
    - r-tidyr
    - r-urltools
    - r-xfun
    - r-xml2

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('emayili')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('emayili')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://datawookie.github.io/emayili/
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: A light, simple tool for sending emails with minimal dependencies.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - ning-y
